# Supabase — Scaling, Replication & Backups Reference

---

## Read Replicas (Pro plan+)

Read replicas are additional read-only copies of your database in different regions.
As of April 2025: GET requests auto-route to the closest replica (geo-routing).

### What changes with read replicas
```
Without replicas:
  All requests → Primary DB (e.g. us-east-1)
  Users in Tokyo → 180ms round trip to US

With replicas + geo-routing (April 2025):
  Read requests → Closest replica (Tokyo gets Japan replica)
  Write requests → Always primary (auto-routed by Supabase)
  Result: Tokyo users → <20ms for reads
```

### Setup
```
Supabase Dashboard → Settings → Add-ons → Read Replicas → Add replica
Choose region(s) closest to your users
```

### Replica endpoints
```typescript
// Each replica has its own endpoint URL
// Supabase client auto-routes reads to closest replica
// No code change needed if using supabase-js

// Manual routing (if you need to force a specific replica):
const replicaClient = createClient(
  process.env.SUPABASE_REPLICA_URL!,    // replica-specific URL from dashboard
  process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY!
)
```

### Critical limitations
```
Read replicas DO work with:
  - supabase-js data queries (SELECT)
  - REST API (GET requests)
  - Realtime subscriptions (as of Q1 2026)

Read replicas do NOT work with:
  - Auth (getUser(), signIn, signOut — always primary)
  - Storage uploads (always primary)
  - Edge Functions that write data
  - Real-time broadcast/presence
```

### Replication lag
```typescript
// Replica can be 1-500ms behind primary
// After a write, reading from replica immediately may return stale data
// Fix: for post-write reads that need to be fresh, route to primary

const { data: newOrder } = await supabase   // write goes to primary
  .from('orders').insert({...}).select().single()

// For the confirmation page after the write — use primary client
// not replica, to avoid showing stale data
const primaryClient = createClient(process.env.SUPABASE_URL!, key)
```

