## Logical Replication (WAL) — Streaming to External Systems

For streaming your Supabase data changes to BigQuery, Redshift, analytics systems,
or another Postgres database in real-time.

### How it works
```
Supabase primary DB
    │
    ▼ WAL (Write-Ahead Log)
Logical replication slot
    │
    ▼ Stream of INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE events
External consumer (BigQuery, Redshift, Airbyte, custom)
```

### Create a publication (defines what to stream)
```sql
-- Stream all tables
CREATE PUBLICATION my_publication FOR ALL TABLES;

-- Stream specific tables only
CREATE PUBLICATION orders_publication FOR TABLE orders, products, profiles;

-- With row filtering (stream only completed orders)
CREATE PUBLICATION completed_orders FOR TABLE orders
WHERE (status = 'completed');
```

### View existing publications
```sql
SELECT pubname, puballtables, pubinsert, pubupdate, pubdelete
FROM pg_publication;
```

### Connect external consumer
```
External system (e.g., Airbyte, Estuary, custom script) connects with:
  host: db.[PROJECT_REF].supabase.co
  port: 5432  (direct connection — replication requires session mode)
  user: postgres
  password: [DB_PASSWORD]
  database: postgres

Then subscribes to the publication:
  CREATE SUBSCRIPTION external_sub
    CONNECTION 'host=... user=postgres dbname=postgres'
    PUBLICATION my_publication;
```

