## Backup Policy

Understanding Supabase backups prevents data loss panic.

| Plan | Backup frequency | Retention | Point-in-time recovery |
|---|---|---|---|
| Free | Daily | 7 days | No |
| Pro | Daily | 30 days | Yes (last 7 days) |
| Team | Daily | 90 days | Yes (last 14 days) |
| Enterprise | Custom | Custom | Yes (custom) |

### Critical: what is NOT backed up
```
Database backups include:
  ✅ All tables and data
  ✅ Functions, triggers, migrations
  ✅ RLS policies and roles
  ✅ Extensions and config

Database backups do NOT include:
  ❌ Files uploaded via Storage API
  ❌ Storage bucket contents
  ❌ Realtime channel history
  ❌ Edge Function logs
```

**Storage files need separate backup**: Export from Supabase → copy to S3 or another bucket.

### Restore from backup
```
Supabase Dashboard → Settings → Backups
→ Select a backup point → Restore
Note: Restore creates a new project — it does not overwrite the current one.
You then migrate data from the restored project to your live project.
```

### Point-in-time recovery (PITR — Pro+)
```
Restore to any minute within the PITR window
Supabase Dashboard → Settings → Backups → Point in Time Recovery
→ Select exact timestamp → Restore to new project
```

