## Compute Tiers — When to Upgrade

| Sign | What it means | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| CPU consistently > 80% | Query load too high | Add indexes, optimize queries, or upgrade compute |
| RAM > 80% | Working sets too large | Increase work_mem carefully, or upgrade |
| Connections hitting limit | Pool exhausted | Ensure port 6543, set max:1 in serverless, or upgrade |
| Read latency > 50ms consistently | Too far from users | Add read replica in user's region |
| Disk I/O maxed | Sequential scans on large tables | Add indexes, or upgrade to get more I/O |

```
Supabase Dashboard → Settings → Compute → Upgrade
Free → Nano → Micro → Small → Medium → Large → XL → 2XL → 4XL → 8XL → 16XL
```
